<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,402,1255]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1014,1039]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1979" box="[665,787,1014,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisselli">
<emphasis box="[665,787,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. grisselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body black; the clypeus wide; the pronotal disc without a transverse pronotal carina; the genitalia with the paramere rounded apically and as long as the basiparamere, and the cuspis with the long arms long, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1979" box="[854,974,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisselli">
<emphasis box="[854,974,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. grisselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body with darkish blue reflection and the metapectal-propodeal disc black; the clypeus with the median lobe angulate and very short; the pronotal disc with a transverse pronotal carina; the genitalia with the paramere wide, angled, and with the ventral margin convex and the dorsal margin sinuous, sparsely setose and longer than the basiparamere, and the cuspis with the long arms short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
